"23:40:4" : {s: 23, a: 40, w: 4, r: "صبح", t: "لَّيُصْبِحُنَّ", l: "أَصْبَحَ", lc: 28, tl: "layuṣ'biḥunna", lb: "হওয়া",e: "surely they will become", b: "অবশ্যই তারা হবে", i: "sungguh mereka akan menjadi", f: 1, rm: "to visit or greet in the morning. subhun/sabahun/isbaahun - the morning. misbaahun (pl. masaabih) - lamp. sabbah (vb. 2) - to come to, come upon, greet, drink in the morning. asbaha - to enter upon the time of the morning, appear, begin to do, to be, become, happen. musbih - one who does anything in or enters upon the morning."},
